condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Amendment of contract with the independent auditor(s) (Section I.A.5 (b) of Schedule 2 to the Loan Agreement) |Description: The Borrower, through ANSES and MDS, shall, prior to carrying out of Part 2.2 (a) (i) (II) of the project, amend thecontract with the independent auditor(s) under terms acceptable to the Bank.

Finance Agreement: Hiring of independent auditors. (Section II.B.4 of Schedule 2) | Description: Not later than six months afterthe Effective Date, and for purposes of validating the actual achievement of the Outputs and review the Unit Costs, the Borrower,through ANSES, shall hire an independent auditor(s) under terms of reference and experience acceptable to the Bank. | Revised DueDate: 30-Jun-2018

Finance Agreement: Municipality Agreements (Section I.A.3.(b) of Schedule 2 to the Loan Agreement) | Description :The Borrowerthrough ANSES and MDS, shall, prior to the carrying out of Part 2.2 (a) of the Project, enter into an agreement with each SelectedMunicipality, under terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date: 31-Aug-2017

Finance Agreement: Registry Agreements (Section I.A.3.(a) of Schedule 2 to the Loan Agreement) | Description :The Borrower throughANSES, shall, prior to the carrying out of Part 2.1 (a) of the Project, enter into an agreement with each Participating Registry,under terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date: 31-Aug-2017

Finance Agreement: Review of Unit Costs (Section I.A.4 of Schedule 2) | Description: The Borrower, through ANSES, shall: (i) notlater than twelve months after the Effective Date and yearly thereafter, review the Unit Costs jointly with the Bank; and (ii)immediately thereafter update said Unit Costs, if applicable, all in a manner acceptable to the Bank. | Frequency: Yearly.
